I don't use the wordpress plugin, but I combined backstretch on my website with the equirejs library (http://wicky.nillia.ms/enquire.js/). So when to "media query" is reached (screen with higher than 1024) backstretch will be applied, otherwise when the screen with is less than 1024 backstretch will be destroyed and the normal css background will be rendered.

``` javascript
enquire.register('screen and (max-width: 1024px)', {
    match: function() {
        $.backstretch('images/background.jpg');
    },
    unmatch: function() {
        $.backstretch('destroy');
    }
});
```

